Investigated this further - it not related to #1534. It's an issue introduced in https://github.com/containers/buildah/commit/c0633e38da4134135d35d32b56194790ca8acecd#diff-65919b07714c5faa770fc0724c4ca886. `securejoin.SecureJoin` drops the trailing slash - which is what [Builder](https://github.com/containers/buildah/blob/master/add.go#L125) uses to determine if target is a folder or a file. I've fixed this by manually restoring the trailing slash if it was present in the original destination spec.

```go
// build.go:495
		if !strings.HasPrefix(finalPath, secureMountPoint) {
			return errors.Wrapf(err, "error resolving copy destination %s", copy.Dest)
		}
		if copy.Dest[len(copy.Dest)-1] == os.PathSeparator {
			finalPath = finalPath + string(os.PathSeparator)
		}
		copy.Dest = strings.TrimPrefix(finalPath, secureMountPoint)
// build.go:501
```
